# VeriMedia AI — Architecture

## System Design

```
Browser
  │
  ▼
Nginx (:80)
  ├── /        → Frontend (React SPA, :5173)
  ├── /api/*   → Backend (FastAPI, :8000)
  └── /ws/*    → WebSocket
         │
         ▼
    FastAPI Backend
         │
    ┌────┴─────────────────────────┐
    │           Pipeline           │
    │  1. Fingerprint              │
    │  2. Similarity (pHash+CLIP)  │
    │  3. ML Classify (6-signal)   │
    │  4. Integrity (9-signal)     │
    │  5. Trust Score              │
    │  6. Propagation Tracking     │
    │  7. Claude AI Analysis       │
    └──────────────────────────────┘
         │
    ┌────┴──────────────────────────────────────┐
    │  PostgreSQL (pgvector)  Redis   MinIO/S3   │
    └───────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

## Decision Flow

```
Detection Result
      │
      ├─ similarity ≥ 88% AND integrity > 75% AND ml=SAFE
      │    └─► ALLOW (green)
      │
      ├─ face_landmark > 70% OR lipsync > 75%
      │    └─► EMERGENCY_TAKEDOWN (red critical)
      │
      ├─ content_type in (news, education) AND sim ≥ 70%
      │    └─► ATTRIBUTION (amber)
      │
      ├─ similarity < 50% AND integrity > 55%
      │    └─► REVIEW REQUIRED (indigo)
      │
      ├─ trust < 40% AND sim > 60%
      │    └─► TAKEDOWN (red)
      │
      ├─ 40% ≤ trust < 65%
      │    └─► SUSPECT (orange)
      │
      └─ trust ≥ 78%
           └─► ALLOW (green)
```

## ML Pipeline — 6 Signals

| Signal | Weight | Description |
|--------|--------|-------------|
| match_score | -2.1 | Visual similarity (lower match = more suspicious) |
| spatial_diff | 1.8 | Pixel-level spatial manipulation |
| color_diff | 1.2 | Color histogram shift |
| frame_diff | 2.3 | Inter-frame inconsistency |
| temporal_diff | 1.9 | Temporal coherence mismatch |
| noise_score | 1.6 | Noise pattern anomaly |
| watermark_detected | -3.4 | Watermark presence (strong negative weight) |

Output: manipulation probability via logistic regression → SAFE / SUSPICIOUS / TAMPERED

## Integrity Analysis — 9 Signals

1. JPEG Artifact — re-compression artifacts
2. Noise Pattern — sensor/encoder fingerprint mismatch
3. Edge Consistency — pixel edge coherence (inverted)
4. Metadata Coherence — EXIF/container consistency (inverted)
5. Color Histogram — palette distribution shift
6. Face Landmark — facial structure distortion (deepfake indicator)
7. Lip-sync — audio-visual alignment (deepfake indicator)
8. Temporal Mismatch — frame timestamp inconsistency
9. Watermark Presence — embedded rights marker (inverted)

## Trust Score

```
trust = 0.55 × similarity + 0.45 × integrity_score
```

## Claude AI Integration

The system sends a structured prompt to `claude-sonnet-4-20250514` with:
- All numerical signals (exact percentages)
- Enforcement decision rules
- Content type context

Claude returns structured JSON with:
- `decision` — enforcement action
- `severity` — LOW/MEDIUM/HIGH/CRITICAL
- `reasoning_points[]` — evidence-cited reasoning (3 points)
- `dmca_needed` — boolean

Fallback: if Claude API is unavailable, the deterministic `_fallback_analysis()` applies the same decision rules locally.
